      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The support for these lessons often centers on creating inclusive environments where every child feels seen and respected for who they are. Proponents argue that teaching about gender identity helps kids understand diversity and build empathy. Conversely, some parents are concerned that this curriculum might introduce concepts too early, potentially interfering with traditional family values or biology, leading to resistance. These differing views highlight a wider societal debate about how sensitive topics should be addressed in K-12 education.",
